{title: Could You}
{artist: Hank Locklin}
{composer: Written by Hank Locklin and Jack Rhodes}

[G]Could you ask me darling for this [C]little gold [G]band
To place on the finger of [A7]another one's [D7]hand
Could you kiss them darling and [G]tell them goodnight
[A7]Let them sleep in the arms that have [D7]held me so tight
[G]Could you ever leave me for [C]somebody [G]new
Oh tell me my [D7]darling could [G]you
Could you pick the roses that [C]I planted [G]there
To place in the curls of [A7]another one's [D7]hair
Could you listen for their footsteps [G]though they are so light
Like [A7]I listen for yours in the [D7]stillness of the night
[G]Could you ever leave me for [C]somebody [G]new
Oh tell me my [D7]darling could [G]you